reviewText: Thought this would be cute for my 10 yr old.  Didn't like the themes and wasn't impressed w/ the story line.  I thought from the other reviews that it would be a good DVD but it's just not something we would bother watching again. Bla.

reviewText: Nothing new and inspiring here.  It's about Santa Claus and some new villian who tries to stop Santa and Christmas.  Ho hum....I got a fourth of the way through and turned it off.  Save your money and buy the kiddies a Rankin Bass DVD like "Rudolph" or "The Year Without a Santa Claus".

reviewText: The animation was good and the story cute, just not up there with the Christmas classics that have been out for decades. You know, Rudolph, Frosty, Santa Claus is Coming to Town, etc. I think children will really enjoy it though so donated it to local VTC center.
summary: Cute, but just not one we'd watch every year
